773	## 2. Anatomy
774	
775	```text
776	TreeView
777	└── Root                           role="tree"
778	    ├── Branch                     role="treeitem" aria-expanded
779	    │   ├── BranchControl        (clickable row; <a> when href present)
780	    │   │   ├── BranchIndicator  aria-hidden="true"
781	    │   │   └── BranchText
782	    │   └── BranchContent        role="group"
783	    │       └── (nested Branch or Leaf nodes)
784	    └── Leaf                       role="treeitem" (aria-expanded when has_children)
785	        └── LeafText             (<a> when href present)
786	```
787	
788	| Part              | Element                               | Key Attributes                                                                                                                                                                                              |
789	| ----------------- | ------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
790	| `Root`            | `<ul>` or `<div>`                     | `data-ars-scope="tree-view"`, `data-ars-part="root"`, `role="tree"`, `aria-multiselectable`                                                                                                                 |
791	| `Branch`          | `<li>` or `<div>`                     | `role="treeitem"`, `aria-expanded` (also set when `has_children` is true with no loaded children), `aria-selected`, `aria-level`, `aria-setsize`, `aria-posinset`, `data-ars-expanded`, `data-ars-selected` |
792	| `BranchControl`   | `<div>` or `<a>` (when href)          | `data-ars-scope="tree-view"`, `data-ars-part="branch-control"`, `href` (when present)                                                                                                                       |
793	| `BranchIndicator` | `<span>`                              | `data-ars-scope="tree-view"`, `data-ars-part="branch-indicator"`, `aria-hidden="true"`, `data-ars-expanded`                                                                                                 |
794	| `BranchText`      | `<span>`                              | `data-ars-scope="tree-view"`, `data-ars-part="branch-text"`                                                                                                                                                 |
795	| `BranchContent`   | `<ul>` or `<div>`                     | `role="group"`, `data-ars-scope="tree-view"`, `data-ars-part="branch-content"`                                                                                                                              |
796	| `Leaf`            | `<li>`, `<div>`, or `<a>` (when href) | `role="treeitem"`, `aria-expanded="false"` (when `has_children` is true), `aria-selected`, `aria-level`, `aria-setsize`, `aria-posinset`, `data-ars-selected`, `href` (when present)                        |
797	| `LeafText`        | `<span>`                              | `data-ars-scope="tree-view"`, `data-ars-part="leaf-text"`                                                                                                                                                   |
798	
799	## 3. Accessibility
800	
801	- While loading, the expandable node shows `aria-busy="true"`.
802	- A visually hidden "Loading" text (from Messages) is announced via `aria-live="polite"`.
803	- On error, the node shows an error state and retry affordance with appropriate `aria-label`.
804	
805	### 3.1 ARIA Roles, States, and Properties
806	
807	| Part            | Role       | Properties                                                                                                                                                                |
808	| --------------- | ---------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
809	| `Root`          | `tree`     | `aria-multiselectable="true"` when `multiple=true`                                                                                                                        |
810	| `Branch`        | `treeitem` | `aria-expanded="true\|false"` (emitted when node has children or `has_children` is true), `aria-selected`, `aria-disabled`, `aria-level`, `aria-setsize`, `aria-posinset` |
811	| `BranchContent` | `group`    | —                                                                                                                                                                         |
812	| `Leaf`          | `treeitem` | `aria-selected`, `aria-disabled`, `aria-level`, `aria-setsize`, `aria-posinset`. When `has_children` is true: also `aria-expanded="false"`                                |
813	
814	When a tree item has an `href`, the adapter renders the clickable area (`BranchControl` or
815	`Leaf`) as an `<a>` element. The `role="treeitem"` on the parent `Branch`/`Leaf` container is
816	preserved — the `<a>` is a descendant of the `role="treeitem"` element, not a replacement for
817	it. This allows native link semantics (middle-click, Ctrl+click) while maintaining the ARIA tree
818	pattern.
819	
820	`aria-level` reflects DOM nesting depth (1-based). `aria-setsize` and `aria-posinset` enable
821	screen readers to announce "item 3 of 5" when navigating.
822	
823	**Parent-child ARIA relationships:** The DOM hierarchy is sufficient to establish parent-child
824	relationships — `aria-owns` is NOT used because children are rendered as direct DOM descendants
825	of their parent treeitem. Branch children are wrapped in a `BranchContent` element with
826	`role="group"` (see anatomy table above), which groups the child treeitems under the parent
827	branch. This `role="group"` container is what allows screen readers to determine nesting
828	without `aria-owns`. If an adapter renders children outside the parent's DOM subtree (e.g., via
829	portals), it MUST add `aria-owns` on the parent `treeitem` referencing the `role="group"`
830	container's ID.
831	
832	### 3.2 Keyboard Interaction
833	
834	| Key                 | Behavior                                                                                                         |
835	| ------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
836	| `ArrowDown`         | Move focus to the next visible node (skips hidden children of collapsed branches).                               |
837	| `ArrowUp`           | Move focus to the previous visible node.                                                                         |
838	| `ArrowRight`        | If focused node is a collapsed branch: expand it. If already expanded (or a leaf): move focus to first child.    |
839	| `ArrowLeft`         | If focused node is an expanded branch: collapse it. If collapsed (or a leaf): move focus to parent.              |
840	| `Home`              | Move focus to the first node in the tree.                                                                        |
841	| `End`               | Move focus to the last visible node in the tree.                                                                 |
842	| `Enter`             | Select the focused node (if `selection_mode != None`).                                                           |
843	| `Space`             | Toggle selection of the focused node (in multiple mode).                                                         |
844	| `*` (asterisk)      | Expand all siblings of the focused node.                                                                         |
845	| `F2`                | Start inline rename on the focused node (when `renamable` is true). See [section 6](#6-variant-renamable-nodes). |
846	| Printable character | Typeahead: jump to the next node whose visible label starts with the typed character.                            |
847	
848	### 3.3 RTL Navigation Semantics
849	
850	`TreeView` keyboard navigation uses **logical** (not visual) semantics that remain consistent regardless of text direction. In both LTR and RTL layouts:
851	
852	- **ArrowRight / ArrowDown** = expand a collapsed branch, or navigate to the first child of an expanded branch.
853	- **ArrowLeft / ArrowUp** = collapse an expanded branch, or navigate to the parent node.
854	
855	This matches the WAI-ARIA `TreeView` pattern, where ArrowRight/ArrowLeft map to expand/collapse (parent-child hierarchy), not to visual direction. The adapter does **not** swap ArrowLeft/ArrowRight in RTL mode for `TreeView`, unlike flat list components (`Accordion`, `Tabs`) where arrows map to next/previous sibling. The rationale is that tree hierarchy is a logical relationship independent of layout direction.
856	
857	### 3.4 Selection Announcements
858	
859	- Selected items have `aria-selected="true"` (already present)
860	- Selection changes are announced via focus movement to the selected node
861	- For programmatic selection changes (no focus change), use LiveAnnouncer:
862	  `announce("{item label} selected", "polite")`
863	
864	### 3.5 Scroll Into View
865	
866	When focus moves to an off-screen tree item, the adapter scrolls it into view using `element.scrollIntoView({ block: 'nearest', inline: 'nearest' })`. For nested scrollable containers, the adapter must walk up the DOM and call `scrollIntoView` on the closest scrollable ancestor only. On iOS Safari, where programmatic focus doesn't trigger scroll, the adapter must explicitly call `scrollIntoView` after `element.focus()`. Smooth scrolling is avoided for keyboard navigation to prevent timing conflicts.
867	
868	### 3.6 Expand/Collapse Keyboard Navigation Race Conditions
869	
870	Rapid keyboard interactions on `TreeView` nodes can cause race conditions between expand/collapse animations and focus movement:
871	
872	1. **Debounce Expansion**: Expand/collapse transitions are not debounced — each ArrowRight (expand) or ArrowLeft (collapse) takes effect immediately. However, the focus movement that follows expansion (ArrowRight on expanded node moves focus to first child) waits until the children are actually rendered.
873	2. **Pending Expansion Guard**: If ArrowRight is pressed on a collapsed node, the node enters an "expanding" state. A second ArrowRight during this state is queued and executed after children render (moving focus to the first child), rather than being ignored.
874	3. **Collapse During Focus-In-Child**: If ArrowLeft collapses a parent while focus is on a child, focus moves to the parent node before the collapse animation starts. The adapter must move focus synchronously, then animate the collapse.
875	4. **Async Children**: For lazily-loaded children (`on_expand` triggers async fetch), the node shows a loading indicator and expansion completes when children arrive. ArrowRight during loading is a no-op.
876	
877	## 4. Internationalization
878	
879	- **RTL**: Arrow key meanings are not reversed for trees (tree nesting is not direction-dependent).
880	  The visual chevron indicator flips via CSS using `[dir="rtl"]`.
881	- **Typeahead**: Character matching is case-insensitive and uses the locale's collation when
882	  available (delegated to `ars-i18n`).
883	- **Label text**: All node labels are consumer-provided. The machine emits a `loading_label` for lazy-loaded branches (see §4.1 Messages).
884	
885	### 4.1 Messages
886	
