907	
908	> **Drag and Drop Reorder**: When `dnd_enabled: true` is set, TreeView integrates with `DraggableCollection<T>` and `DroppableCollection<T>` from `06-collections.md` §7. This adds optional `drag::Handle` and `drop::Indicator` anatomy parts. TreeView supports both `CollectionDndEvent::Reorder` (reordering siblings) and `CollectionDndEvent::Move` (reparenting nodes by dropping onto a parent item with `drop::Position::On`).
909	
910	### 4.2 Drag-Reorder Behavior
911	
912	When drag-and-drop reorder is enabled (`dnd_enabled: true`), the following behaviors apply:
913	
914	- **Drag handle**: Each tree item renders an optional drag handle affordance (the `drag::Handle` anatomy part). The handle is the grab target; the entire row is not draggable by default to avoid conflicts with text selection.
915	- **Hover-expand**: When dragging over a collapsed tree node, the node automatically expands after a 500ms hover delay. This allows users to drop items into nested levels without manually expanding first.
916	- **Drop target indication**: Valid drop zones are visually highlighted during drag. Three drop positions are supported:
917	  - `Before` — insert before the target node (horizontal line above)
918	  - `After` — insert after the target node (horizontal line below)
919	  - `Child` — insert as a child of the target node (target node background highlight)
920	- **Drop position detection**: The drop position is determined by the pointer's vertical position within the target row: top 25% = `Before`, bottom 25% = `After`, middle 50% = `Child`.
921	- **Keyboard drag**: Full keyboard support for reordering:
922	  - `Enter` or `Space` on a focused drag handle to pick up the item
923	  - Arrow keys to move the item through valid drop positions
924	  - `Enter` to confirm the drop
925	  - `Escape` to cancel and return the item to its original position
926	- **Reorder callback**: `on_reorder: Callback<ReorderEvent>` fires when a drop is completed.
927	
928	```rust
929	/// Event emitted when a tree item is reordered via drag-and-drop.
930	#[derive(Clone, Debug, PartialEq)]
931	pub struct ReorderEvent {
932	    /// Path of the dragged item (sequence of keys from root to item).
933	    pub source_path: Vec<Key>,
934	    /// Path of the drop target.
935	    pub target_path: Vec<Key>,
936	    /// Where relative to the target the item was dropped.
937	    pub position: DropPosition,
938	}
939	
940	// `DropPosition` — defined in `06-collections.md`
941	```
942	
943	## 5. Variant: Lazy Loading
944	
945	`TreeView` supports lazy loading of child nodes for large or server-driven hierarchies. When a node is first expanded and its children are not yet loaded, the machine fires a `LoadChildren` event.
946	
947	### 5.1 Additional Props
948	
949	```rust,no_check
950	/// The load_children callback is registered in the adapter layer, not in Props.
951	/// When provided, nodes without pre-loaded children will trigger lazy loading on expand.
952	/// The adapter observes `LoadChildren(Key)` events and calls the user-provided callback.
953	```
954	
955	```rust
956	/// Type alias for the lazy-load callback.
957	/// The adapter calls this with the parent node's key when children need loading.
958	/// The callback should eventually send a `ChildrenLoaded` event back to the machine.
959	/// Uses `Rc` so the adapter can clone it into event handler closures.
960	pub type LoadChildrenFn = Rc<dyn Fn(Key)>;
961	```
962	
963	### 5.2 Additional Events
964	
965	```rust,no_check
966	/// Added to TreeView Event enum.
967	/// Fired when a node is expanded for the first time and has no children loaded.
968	LoadChildren(Key),
969	/// Fired by the consumer (via adapter callback) when lazy-loaded children arrive.
970	ChildrenLoaded {
971	    /// The parent node key.
972	    parent: Key,
973	    /// The loaded children nodes.
974	    children: Vec<Node<T>>,
975	},
976	```
977	
978	### 5.3 Additional Node State
979	
980	```rust
981	/// Extended NodeState to include loading.
982	#[derive(Clone, Copy, Debug, PartialEq)]
983	pub enum NodeLoadState {
984	    /// Children are present in the collection.
985	    Loaded,
986	    /// Children are being fetched (loading indicator shown).
987	    Loading,
988	    /// Load failed — adapter may show retry affordance.
989	    Error,
990	    /// Children have not been requested yet (initial state for lazy nodes).
991	    NotLoaded,
992	}
993	```
994	
995	The `tree_view::Context` tracks `load_state: BTreeMap<Key, NodeLoadState>`.
996	
997	### 5.4 Behavior
998	
999	1. User expands a node whose `load_state` is `NotLoaded`.
1000	2. Machine transitions `load_state` to `Loading` and fires `LoadChildren(key)`.
1001	3. Adapter calls `load_children(key)` prop. The consumer fetches data asynchronously.
1002	4. Consumer sends `ChildrenLoaded { parent, children }` when data arrives.
1003	5. Machine inserts children into the collection and transitions `load_state` to `Loaded`.
1004	6. If loading fails, consumer sends `LoadError(key)` and machine transitions to `Error`.
1005	
1006	## 6. Variant: Renamable Nodes
1007	
1008	`TreeView` supports inline rename of tree nodes, similar to file-explorer rename behavior.
1009	When enabled, users can start renaming a node via F2 or slow double-click. The node's text
1010	display is replaced by an inline `<input>` element until the rename is committed or cancelled.
1011	
1012	### 6.1 Additional Props
1013	
1014	```rust,no_check
1015	/// Additional props for the renamable variant.
1016	impl Props {
1017	    /// When true, tree items can be renamed inline via F2 or slow double-click.
1018	    /// Default: `false`.
1019	    pub renamable: bool,
1020	}
1021	
1022	// In Props::default():
1023	// renamable: false,
1024	```
1025	
1026	### 6.2 Additional Events
1027	
1028	```rust,no_check
1029	/// Added to TreeView Event enum for the renamable variant.
1030	
1031	/// User initiates rename on a node (e.g., F2 or slow double-click).
1032	RenameStart(Key),
1033	/// User commits the new name.
1034	RenameCommit { key: Key, new_name: String },
1035	/// User cancels rename (Escape or blur without change).
1036	RenameCancel(Key),
1037	```
1038	
1039	### 6.3 Additional Context
1040	
1041	```rust,no_check
1042	/// Added to TreeView Context for the renamable variant.
1043	impl Context {
1044	    /// The node currently being renamed, if any. When `Some(key)`, the node
1045	    /// identified by `key` renders a `NodeRenameInput` instead of its text label.
1046	    pub renaming_key: Option<Key>,
1047	}
1048	
1049	// In Machine::init():
1050	// renaming_key: None,
1051	```
1052	
1053	### 6.4 Behavior
1054	
1055	- **`RenameStart(key)`**: Only allowed from `Idle` or `Focused` states. If `renamable` is
1056	  false or the target node is disabled, the event is ignored. If another node is currently
1057	  being renamed (`renaming_key` is `Some(other_key)`), that rename is committed first (fires
1058	  `RenameCommit` for the previous node with its current input value), then `renaming_key` is
1059	  set to `Some(key)`. Focus moves to the rename input.
1060	- **`RenameCommit { key, new_name }`**: Clears `renaming_key` to `None`. The consumer is
1061	  responsible for persisting the new name (e.g., updating the `TreeCollection` data source).
1062	  The machine does not modify the `TreeItem.label` — the consumer updates the collection and
1063	  passes new props.
1064	- **`RenameCancel(key)`**: Clears `renaming_key` to `None`. No value change occurs. Focus
1065	  returns to the tree item that was being renamed.
1066	
1067	```rust,no_check
1068	/// Transition logic for rename events.
1069	/// Added to the Machine::transition match block.
1070	
1071	Event::RenameStart(key) => {
1072	    if !_props.renamable { return None; }
1073	    let node_disabled = ctx.items.get(key)
1074	        .and_then(|n| n.value.as_ref())
1075	        .map(|v| v.disabled)
1076	        .unwrap_or(false);
1077	    if node_disabled { return None; }
1078	    match state {
1079	        State::Idle | State::Focused => {
1080	            let key = key.clone();
1081	            Some(TransitionPlan::to(State::Focused).apply(move |ctx| {
1082	                ctx.renaming_key = Some(key.clone());
1083	                ctx.focused_node = Some(key);
1084	            }))
1085	        }
1086	        _ => None,
1087	    }
1088	}
1089	
1090	Event::RenameCommit { key, .. } => {
1091	    if ctx.renaming_key.as_ref() != Some(key) { return None; }
1092	    Some(TransitionPlan::context_only(|ctx| {
1093	        ctx.renaming_key = None;
1094	    }))
1095	}
1096	
1097	Event::RenameCancel(key) => {
1098	    if ctx.renaming_key.as_ref() != Some(key) { return None; }
1099	    Some(TransitionPlan::context_only(|ctx| {
1100	        ctx.renaming_key = None;
1101	    }))
1102	}
1103	```
1104	
1105	### 6.5 Anatomy Additions
1106	
1107	```text
1108	TreeView (renamable variant)
1109	└── Root
1110	    ├── Branch
1111	    │   ├── BranchControl
1112	    │   │   ├── BranchIndicator
1113	    │   │   ├── BranchText           (hidden when renaming_key matches)
1114	    │   │   └── NodeRenameInput(key)   (shown when renaming_key matches)
1115	    │   └── BranchContent
1116	    └── Leaf
1117	        ├── LeafText                 (hidden when renaming_key matches)
1118	        └── NodeRenameInput(key)       (shown when renaming_key matches)
1119	```
1120	
1121	The `NodeRenameInput(Key)` part is an `<input type="text">` element rendered inside the
1122	branch control or leaf when `renaming_key == Some(key)`. It replaces the text display during
1123	rename and is pre-filled with the node's current `label` value.
1124	
1125	```rust,no_check
1126	/// Added to Part enum.
1127	NodeRenameInput { node_id: String },
1128	```
1129	
1130	```rust
1131	/// Attrs for the inline rename input.
1132	/// Rendered only when `renaming_key == Some(key)` for this node.
1133	pub fn node_rename_input_attrs(&self, node_id: &str) -> AttrMap {
1134	    let mut attrs = AttrMap::new();
1135	    let [(scope_attr, scope_val), (part_attr, part_val)] =
1136	        Part::NodeRenameInput { node_id: Default::default() }.data_attrs();
1137	    attrs.set(scope_attr, scope_val);
1138	    attrs.set(part_attr, part_val);
1139	    let label = self.get_node(node_id)
1140	        .and_then(|n| n.value.as_ref())
1141	        .map(|v| v.label.as_str())
1142	        .unwrap_or("");
1143	    attrs.set(HtmlAttr::Type, "text");
1144	    attrs.set(HtmlAttr::Value, label);
1145	    attrs.set(
1146	        HtmlAttr::Aria(AriaAttr::Label),
1147	        (self.ctx.messages.rename_label)(label, &self.ctx.locale),
1148	    );
1149	    attrs
1150	}
1151	
1152	/// Handle keydown events on the rename input.
1153	pub fn on_rename_input_keydown(&self, node_id: &str, key_code: &str, current_value: &str) {
1154	    match key_code {
1155	        "Enter" => {
1156	            (self.send)(Event::RenameCommit {
1157	                key: Key::from(node_id),
1158	                new_name: current_value.to_string(),
1159	            });
1160	        }
1161	        "Escape" => {
1162	            (self.send)(Event::RenameCancel(Key::from(node_id)));
1163	        }
1164	        _ => {}
1165	    }
1166	}
1167	
1168	/// Handle blur on the rename input — commits the rename if still active.
1169	pub fn on_rename_input_blur(&self, node_id: &str, current_value: &str) {
1170	    let key = Key::from(node_id);
1171	    if self.ctx.renaming_key.as_ref() == Some(&key) {
1172	        (self.send)(Event::RenameCommit {
1173	            key,
1174	            new_name: current_value.to_string(),
1175	        });
1176	    }
1177	}
1178	
1179	/// Check if a node is currently being renamed.
1180	pub fn is_renaming(&self, node_id: &str) -> bool {
1181	    self.ctx.renaming_key.as_ref().map(|k| k.as_ref()) == Some(node_id)
1182	}
1183	```
1184	
1185	The `part_attrs` match is extended:
1186	
1187	```rust,no_check
1188	Part::NodeRenameInput { ref node_id } => self.node_rename_input_attrs(node_id),
1189	```
1190	
1191	### 6.6 Accessibility
1192	
1193	| Key      | Behavior                                                       |
1194	| -------- | -------------------------------------------------------------- |
1195	| `F2`     | Start rename on the focused node (when `renamable` is true).   |
1196	| `Enter`  | Commit the rename (when rename input is focused).              |
1197	| `Escape` | Cancel the rename, discard changes, return focus to tree item. |
1198	
1199	- The `NodeRenameInput` receives `aria-label` from `Messages.rename_label`, which receives
1200	  the node's current label as the first argument. Screen readers announce e.g.,
1201	  "Rename Documents" when focus enters the input.
1202	- When rename starts, focus moves to the `NodeRenameInput`. When rename ends (commit or
1203	  cancel), focus returns to the tree item.
1204	- The rename input is not part of the tab sequence (`tabindex="-1"` is not needed because
1205	  it is a native `<input>` that receives focus programmatically).
1206	
1207	### 6.7 Messages
1208	
1209	```rust,no_check
1210	/// Added to the Messages struct for the renamable variant.
1211	impl Messages {
1212	    /// Accessible label for the rename input. Called with the node's current
1213	    /// label and the resolved locale.
1214	    /// Default: `|node_name, _locale| format!("Rename {}", node_name)`
1215	    pub rename_label: MessageFn<dyn Fn(&str, &Locale) -> String + Send + Sync>,
1216	}
1217	
1218	// In Messages::default():
1219	// rename_label: MessageFn::new(|node_name, _locale| format!("Rename {}", node_name)),
1220	```
1221	
1222	## 7. Library Parity
1223	
1224	> Compared against: Ark UI (`TreeView`), React Aria (`Tree`).
1225	
1226	### 7.1 Props
1227	
1228	| Feature             | ars-ui                             | Ark UI                                 | React Aria                     | Notes                                       |
1229	| ------------------- | ---------------------------------- | -------------------------------------- | ------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------- |
1230	| Tree data source    | `items: TreeCollection<TreeItem>`  | `collection: TreeCollection<T>`        | `items: Iterable<T>`           | All provide collection-based API            |
1231	| Controlled selected | `selected`                         | --                                     | `selectedKeys`                 | Ark uses context API                        |
1232	| Default selected    | `default_selected`                 | `defaultSelectedValue`                 | `defaultSelectedKeys`          | Full match                                  |
1233	| Controlled expanded | `expanded`                         | `expandedValue`                        | `expandedKeys`                 | Full match                                  |
1234	| Default expanded    | `default_expanded`                 | `defaultExpandedValue`                 | `defaultExpandedKeys`          | Full match                                  |
1235	| Selection mode      | `selection_mode`                   | `selectionMode`                        | `selectionMode`                | Full match                                  |
1236	| Selection behavior  | `selection_behavior`               | --                                     | `selectionBehavior`            | ars-ui matches React Aria                   |
1237	| Multiple selection  | `multiple`                         | --                                     | --                             | Expressed via `selection_mode` in all       |
1238	| Disabled keys       | per-item `disabled` field          | --                                     | `disabledKeys`                 | ars-ui uses per-item field in TreeItem      |
1239	| Disabled behavior   | --                                 | --                                     | `disabledBehavior`             | See below                                   |
1240	| Typeahead           | via `TypeaheadSearch` event        | `typeahead`                            | --                             | ars-ui always has typeahead                 |
1241	| Expand on click     | via `on_branch_control_click`      | `expandOnClick`                        | --                             | ars-ui expands on click by default          |
1242	| Lazy loading        | `LoadChildren` variant (section 5) | `loadChildren`                         | --                             | ars-ui has full lazy-load variant           |
1243	| Renamable           | `renamable` variant (section 6)    | `canRename`                            | --                             | ars-ui has full renamable variant           |
1244	| Checked (checkbox)  | --                                 | `checkedValue` / `defaultCheckedValue` | --                             | See below                                   |
1245	| DnD                 | DnD variant (section 4.2)          | --                                     | `dragAndDropHooks`             | ars-ui has full DnD variant                 |
1246	| Escape key behavior | --                                 | --                                     | `escapeKeyBehavior`            | See below                                   |
1247	| Virtualization      | --                                 | `scrollToIndexFn`                      | --                             | Adapter-level concern                       |
1248	| Focused value       | --                                 | `focusedValue` / `defaultFocusedValue` | --                             | ars-ui tracks via `focused_node` in Context |
1249	| Has children flag   | `TreeItem.has_children`            | --                                     | `hasChildItems` (per TreeItem) | Full match                                  |
1250	| Node href           | `TreeItem.href`                    | --                                     | `href` (per TreeItem)          | ars-ui matches React Aria                   |
1251	| Empty state         | --                                 | --                                     | `renderEmptyState`             | Adapter concern                             |
1252	| On action           | --                                 | --                                     | `onAction`                     | See below                                   |
1253	
1254	**Gaps:**
1255	
1256	- **`disabledBehavior`**: React Aria supports `'all' | 'selection'` to control whether disabled items block all interaction or only selection. ars-ui disabled items block all interaction. Low priority -- `'selection'` mode is niche.
1257	- **`checkedValue` (tri-state checkboxes)**: Ark UI supports per-node checkboxes with `checked`/`unchecked`/`indeterminate` states, including `NodeCheckbox` and `NodeCheckboxIndicator` anatomy. ars-ui could add this as a variant, but it is a specialized use case. Low priority.
1258	- **`escapeKeyBehavior`**: React Aria allows `'clearSelection' | 'none'` on Escape press. ars-ui does not currently handle Escape in the tree. Low priority.
1259	- **`onAction`**: React Aria fires `onAction(Key)` when a tree item is activated (Enter/click). ars-ui handles this via `SelectNode` event. The consumer can observe selection changes. Low priority.
1260	
1261	### 7.2 Anatomy
1262	
1263	| Part                | ars-ui            | Ark UI                                   | React Aria                   | Notes                              |
1264	| ------------------- | ----------------- | ---------------------------------------- | ---------------------------- | ---------------------------------- |
1265	| Root                | `Root`            | `Root`                                   | `Tree`                       | Full match                         |
1266	| Label               | --                | `Label`                                  | --                           | Ark has optional tree label        |
1267	| Tree list           | --                | `Tree`                                   | --                           | Ark separates Root from Tree list  |
1268	| Branch node         | `Branch`          | `Branch`                                 | `TreeItem` (with children)   | Full match                         |
1269	| Branch control      | `BranchControl`   | `BranchControl`                          | --                           | ars-ui and Ark have this           |
1270	| Branch indicator    | `BranchIndicator` | `BranchIndicator`                        | --                           | ars-ui and Ark have this           |
1271	| Branch text         | `BranchText`      | `BranchText`                             | --                           | ars-ui and Ark have this           |
1272	| Branch content      | `BranchContent`   | `BranchContent`                          | --                           | ars-ui and Ark have this           |
1273	| Branch indent guide | --                | `BranchIndentGuide`                      | --                           | Purely visual; adapter concern     |
1274	| Leaf node           | `Leaf`            | `Item`                                   | `TreeItem` (no children)     | Full match                         |
1275	| Leaf text           | `LeafText`        | `ItemText`                               | --                           | ars-ui and Ark have this           |
1276	| Node checkbox       | --                | `NodeCheckbox` / `NodeCheckboxIndicator` | --                           | Ark-only tri-state checkbox        |
1277	| Rename input        | `NodeRenameInput` | `NodeRenameInput`                        | --                           | ars-ui and Ark have this           |
1278	| Node provider       | --                | `NodeProvider`                           | --                           | Ark-specific context provider      |
1279	| Item content        | --                | --                                       | `TreeItemContent`            | React Aria render prop wrapper     |
1280	| Section             | --                | --                                       | `TreeSection` / `TreeHeader` | React Aria grouping; not in ars-ui |
1281	| Load more item      | --                | --                                       | `TreeLoadMoreItem`           | React Aria infinite scroll trigger |
1282	
1283	**Gaps:**
1284	
1285	- **`BranchIndentGuide`**: Ark UI has a dedicated indent guide part for rendering vertical tree lines. This is purely a CSS/visual concern and can be achieved via CSS `::before` pseudo-elements on Branch nodes in ars-ui. Not worth adding as a formal part.
1286	- **`Label`**: Ark UI has a `Label` part for the tree's accessible name. ars-ui achieves this via `aria-label` or `aria-labelledby` on the Root element, which is the standard ARIA approach. No gap.
1287	- **`TreeSection` / `TreeHeader`**: React Aria supports grouping tree items into labeled sections. This is an advanced composition pattern; consumers can achieve this by structuring their TreeCollection data appropriately. Low priority.
1288	
1289	### 7.3 Events
1290	
1291	| Callback            | ars-ui                | Ark UI                   | React Aria          | Notes                         |
1292	| ------------------- | --------------------- | ------------------------ | ------------------- | ----------------------------- |
1293	| Selection change    | `Bindable` onChange   | `onSelectionChange`      | `onSelectionChange` | ars-ui uses Bindable pattern  |
1294	| Expanded change     | `Bindable` onChange   | `onExpandedChange`       | `onExpandedChange`  | ars-ui uses Bindable pattern  |
1295	| Focus change        | `Focus`/`Blur` events | `onFocusChange`          | --                  | ars-ui and Ark track focus    |
1296	| Checked change      | --                    | `onCheckedChange`        | --                  | Ark-only; see checkbox gap    |
1297	| Rename start        | `RenameStart`         | `onRenameStart`          | --                  | ars-ui and Ark have this      |
1298	| Rename complete     | `RenameCommit`        | `onRenameComplete`       | --                  | ars-ui and Ark have this      |
1299	| Before rename       | --                    | `onBeforeRename`         | --                  | Ark has pre-rename validation |
1300	| Load children done  | `ChildrenLoaded`      | `onLoadChildrenComplete` | --                  | ars-ui and Ark have this      |
1301	| Load children error | `LoadError` (implied) | `onLoadChildrenError`    | --                  | ars-ui and Ark have this      |
1302	| Action              | --                    | --                       | `onAction`          | React Aria item activation    |
1303	
1304	**Gaps:** None that need addressing. `onBeforeRename` can be implemented by the consumer handling `RenameStart` and conditionally allowing it. `onAction` is covered by `SelectNode` semantics.
1305	
1306	### 7.4 Features
1307	
1308	| Feature                      | ars-ui        | Ark UI            | React Aria  |
1309	| ---------------------------- | ------------- | ----------------- | ----------- |
1310	| Expand/collapse              | Yes           | Yes               | Yes         |
1311	| Single/multiple selection    | Yes           | Yes               | Yes         |
1312	| Keyboard navigation (arrows) | Yes           | Yes               | Yes         |
1313	| Typeahead search             | Yes           | Yes               | No          |
1314	| Drag and drop                | Yes (variant) | No                | Yes         |
1315	| Lazy loading                 | Yes (variant) | Yes               | No          |
1316	| Inline rename                | Yes (variant) | Yes               | No          |
1317	| RTL support                  | Yes           | Yes               | Yes         |
1318	| Per-node disabled            | Yes           | Yes               | Yes         |
1319	| Tri-state checkboxes         | No            | Yes               | No          |
1320	| Virtualization               | Adapter-level | `scrollToIndexFn` | Virtualizer |
1321	| Expand all / collapse all    | Yes           | Via context API   | No          |
1322	
1323	**Gaps:** Tri-state checkboxes (Ark-only) are a specialized feature not essential for v1.
1324	
1325	### 7.5 Summary
1326	
1327	- **Overall:** Full parity with React Aria. Near-full parity with Ark UI (missing tri-state checkboxes).
1328	- **Divergences:** ars-ui uses per-item `disabled` field in `TreeItem` rather than a `disabledKeys` set (React Aria style). Ark's `BranchIndentGuide` is a CSS concern. ars-ui separates lazy loading and rename into explicit variants rather than always-available props.
1329	- **Recommended additions:** None for v1. Tri-state node checkboxes could be added as a future variant if demand warrants.
1330

